Rating: 3
This was my first bread pudding attempt. I thought it came out a bit soggy after 30 minutes in the oven so would cook five minutes longer next time. I also used rum instead of grappa, and didn't bother sauteeing it as the prunes soaked up the rum and no extra liquid remained (but maybe explains why it was soggy?). I'd tweak it a bit if I made it again, but it's definitely worth experimenting with because the panettone really works beautifully.

Rating: 3
I made this recipe slightly adjusted to reduce the amount of lactose. It came out great using a combination of whole lactose free milk and goat's milk. Overall, I found it to be pretty good and easy. This was the first bread pudding I've ever made, but it wasn't the best that I've ever had.

