Rating: 4
this is a fabulous recipe! I simplified it by just cubing the toasted bread and folding it, as well as grappa-macerated raisins (instead of prunes) into the egg mixture. I also skipped the water bath. it still came out beautifully and deliciously.

Rating: 4
I'm not a big fan of bread pudding, but this was fabulous. I used rum too (didn't have grappa), and a nice Easter pannetone with a lot of orange rind in it. It was an amazing Easter dessert, and very easy.

