Wonderful recipe. The only change I made was to substitute rum for the grappa. It was delicious! If you like bread pudding - make sure and try this one.

Rating: 4
I have made lots of bread puddings and I am quite picky about them. I have to say that this is one of the best recipes I have made! Perfect consistency and flavor.

Rating: 4
This was really delicious. I substituted dried cherries for the prunes which, although expensive, was well worth it, and I served it with a homemade chestnut ice cream. This was even better the next day served cold, I couldn't keep my hands off it. A great way to use up that leftover Pannetone. Elegant comfort food at it's best. Be careful when toating the bread, it browns very quickly.